				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: 2016 is the Year of VR
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1849183">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Wireless Internet.<br />
Cloud Infrastructure.<br />
Virtual Reality.<br />
<br />
After almost a decade of people crowing about how wireless was the future, we've FINALLY GOTTEN to the point where it's marginally functional for most uses. (Still sucks ass at latency and is interfered with by christmas lights and microwaves for home stuff, so save that document you're working on while you're on the VPN over Wi-Fi! but the roaming bluetooth stuff is pretty cool)<br />
<br />
Cloud anything is at least 5 years off in most markets strictly because of local infrastructure SUCKING OUT LOUD on the internet side of things. After all, the only thing cloud means is &quot;someone else's datacenter&quot;.<br />
<br />
VR is about a decade out for full immersion and adoption.<br />
<br />
2016 is the year of selling advertising space on stuff like <a href="http://www.informationweek.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.informationweek.com/</a> the same way it has been every other year, but it's going to take a LOT of technical work before anyone is using VR practically on a day-to-day basis.<br />
<br />
For now, it's just youtube videos and pretty color printouts in targeted rags.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
